cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DC 

The paper deals with interference and capacity analysis in small cell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves probability and statistics, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the feasibility of shared and dedicated spectrum access, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
